Therefore, the new module will take both cin and ratio as inputs. It will perform the same operations as SE_LN but with the reduction factor determined by the ratio parameter instead of being fixed at 2.

This approach allows more flexibility. For example, if someone wants a higher compression ratio (like 4), they can set ratio=4, making the module more efficient in terms of computation since fewer neurons are used in the bottleneck layer. At the same time, the inclusion of LayerNorm could help in stabilizing the training process by normalizing the activations after the first FC layer.

