 about the modifications made to the original code:

The original SE module used only average pooling, while the modified version uses both average and max pooling. This change increases the model's ability to capture different types of features, which likely improves performance.

Additionally, the modified code introduced Mish activation instead of ReLU, which is known for better gradient flow and potentially higher accuracy.

Moreover, a dropout layer was added after the first fully connected layer. Dropout helps prevent overfitting by randomly deactivating neurons during training, leading to more robust models.

Finally, the number of channels processed was doubled by concatenating average and max pooled features before feeding them into the FC layers. This increased the capacity of the network without significantly increasing computational cost.

All these changes contribute to better model performance, likely improving metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, etc.

